text=(:if [ authgroup @tas || authgroup @admins || equal {$Author} '' ]:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=edit|Edit this page]] \\%0aStatus: {GradebookArticles.{$Name}$:Status} %0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!{$:Category}]]%0a%0a!Importance of sign language for all deaf babies%0a%0a:Author: savannah%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0a The misconception that learning sign language could hamper language development hinders speech development%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aFamilies with deaf children face decisions about education and language. In many cases, when newborns fail a hearing test and are candidates for cochlear implants, small electronic devices that allow severely deaf people to perceive sounds through the stimulation of auditory nerves, parents are often told to speak to the babies as if they were normal to prevent delay in spoken language development (1). However, research show that implanted deaf children often ends up with limited language skills (1). %0a%0aIt should be noted that hearing through a cochlear implant is not like normal hearing and requires training for the brain to comprehend to sound it perceives (1). Moreover, the understanding of speech among implanted people is variable, and sign language is shown to accelerate language development in implanted children (2). Research conducted on a group of first-generation and second-generation cochlear-implanted children showed that second-generation deaf children performed better on language development tests, suggesting that teaching deaf children sign language before cochlear implantation is beneficial to language development (2). Therefore, it can be seen how the misconception that learning sign language could hamper language development hinders speech development (1). Additionally, sign language must be introduced to children as early as possible because there is an optimum age for acquiring languages, including sign language (1). Similar to the decline in one’s ability to learn a new language after a certain age, studies have shown cases where deaf children with later sign language exposure had difficulty learning complex sign language grammatical structures (1).%0a%0aPeople should be aware that learning sign language does not hinder a child’s spoken language development. And to prevent a delay in language development, families of deaf babies should introduce deaf children to sign language as early as possible (1).%0a1. https://www.nidcd.nih.gov/health/cochlear-implants%0a2. https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/journal-of-laryngology-and-otology/article/outcomes-of-cochlear-implantation-in-deaf-children-of-deaf-parents-comparative-study/A949F20D96D996073FBB47590F4F85F2%0a%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a#foxbegin 221202-082427-194770#%0a(:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a!!!Importance of sign language for babies %0a-> - benjaminlu%0a-> [-02.12.2022 - 00:24-]%0a>>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a(:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a{[foxdelrange button 221202-082427-194770 {$FullName} ]}%0a(:if1end:)%0a>>%3c%3c%0a(:div1end:) %0a>>messageitem%3c%3c %0aNot only is sign language beneficial to deaf babies, it is also vital to normal babies. Based on research, sign language speeds up speech development as it allows the brain to start developing at a younger age. Babies who learn sign language tend to express themselves better; even if they do not know how to speak, they can convey their thoughts clearly through signs. This allows parents to bond better with their babies through more effective communication. It is also stated that infants who learn sign language gain several psychological benefits. Infants who learn sign language are more confident than those who do not. All in all, sign language is crucial for babies, as it benefits their development and promotes family relations.%0a%0ahttps://www.educationalplaycare.com/blog/sign-language-benefits-for-young-children/#:~:text=Research%2520shows%2520that%2520sign%2520language,they%2520are%2520hurt%2520or%2520hungry.%0a%0ahttps://www.cceionline.com/the-benefits-of-sign-language-for-preschoolers/%0a%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a#foxend 221202-082427-194770#%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%0aYou must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a%0a----%0a(:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a!!Change article category%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a%0a(:Section: A:)%0a(:Category: SignLanguage:)%0a(:Title: Importance of sign language for all deaf babies:)
